const description = "Fisher & Paykel refrigerator, dishwasher, washer & dryer repair in LA. Same-day service, OEM parts. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What Fisher & Paykel appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "The full F&P US lineup. French door refrigerators (RF170 / RF201 / RF522 series — including the integrated column refrigerators specified into custom kitchens), DishDrawer dishwashers (the patented drawer-format machine, single DD24 and double DD60 configurations), front-load washers and condenser/heat-pump dryers (WH and DE series), ranges (OR series — induction, dual-fuel, and gas variants in 30, 36, 48-inch widths), gas and induction cooktops (CI / CG series), wall ovens (OB series — single and double, the OB60 induction-platform integrated cooking platform), and range hoods (HC series — both wall and island configurations). What we cover spans every category Fisher & Paykel actively sells in the US market. The DishDrawer is the brand's signature differentiator and the category most LA customers know F&P for; the refrigerator and laundry sides are where the bulk of our actual service hours land."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Fisher & Paykel appliance repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. Common F&P repairs: DishDrawer latch mechanism replacement $245-$385 (the most common F&P service item across our LA route — the 2016-2021 DD60 cohort develops this consistently around year 5-6); DishDrawer wash motor $345-$525; DishDrawer control board $345-$525; refrigerator ActiveSmart main control board $385-$585 (different diagnostic path than a simple thermostat fault — see FAQ #4); evaporator fan motor on RF-series refrigerators $245-$385; ice maker assembly $345-$525; door gasket replacement $185-$285; washer drum bearing on the WH-series front-loads $585-$885 (a larger job — bearing failure usually means tub-out service); washer drain pump $245-$385; dryer heating element on the DE-series $185-$285; range igniter / spark module on OR-series gas ranges $185-$285; induction generator board on induction OR variants $485-$685; range hood blower motor $285-$425; wall oven door hinge $185-$285. Compressor or sealed-system work on out-of-warranty refrigerators (year 10+) runs $680-$980. Parts ship from F&P's US distribution under the Haier network — typical 5-10 day lead time for less-common items, common DishDrawer / RF-series wear parts on the truck for same-day completion."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you repair the Fisher & Paykel DishDrawer?",
    a: "Yes — DishDrawer is our highest-volume F&P service category, and the work is genuinely different from any standard dishwasher repair. The DishDrawer is a patented drawer-format machine F&P invented in 1997: instead of the full-height tub with a drop-down door, each drawer is its own independent washing chamber with its own water inlet, drain, wash motor, control board, and seal system. Double DD60 configurations stack two of these as independent appliances — you can run the top drawer with delicate glassware while the bottom does a heavy pots-and-pans cycle in parallel. <strong>This architecture means DishDrawer repair is a different service tree than any standard machine</strong>. The dominant failure pattern: 2016-2021 DD60 latch mechanism wear around year 5-6, with the left drawer (which on most installations carries heavier daily use because of how counter-flow patterns work) failing first in double configurations. Symptoms: drawer won't latch closed, cycle won't start, sometimes a partial latch that triggers mid-cycle and aborts. Replacement runs $245-$385 per drawer, often same-day when we stock the common DD60 latch on the truck. Beyond the latch pattern, the DishDrawer service tree includes wash motor (year 7-9), control board (year 8-10), drawer seal compression (year 4-6), and the small water inlet solenoid that's specific to the drawer format. Our techs know which subsystem belongs to which drawer — important on double DD60 service where one drawer can run perfectly while the other needs work."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the most common Fisher & Paykel repair?",
    a: "DishDrawer latch mechanism on the 2016-2021 DD60 double-drawer cohort — by a wide margin. The drawer latch is the gate that triggers cycle start, and it cycles every time the user closes the drawer. Across roughly five years of use the mechanism develops wear that produces inconsistent latching, eventually failing to engage at all. Left drawer fails first in most double installations (heavier-use patterning), right drawer typically follows 12-18 months later. After the DishDrawer latch, the next most common F&P service items in our LA mix are: (2) refrigerator ActiveSmart control board on the RF-series — when the ActiveSmart system stops adapting properly the unit runs as if it's stuck in default mode, often presenting as inconsistent temperatures or over-cooling in one compartment. Different repair path than a simple thermostat fault (the ActiveSmart board is the entire adaptive-learning brain, not a temperature sensor). (3) Washer drum bearing on the WH-series front-loads, year 7-10 — larger job (tub disassembly) but well within repair territory given the unit's replacement cost. (4) Dryer heating element on the condenser DE-series, year 6-8. The other categories (ranges, cooktops, range hoods, wall ovens) generate steadier but lower-volume service work — F&P cooking lineup is built solid and the failure timelines stretch longer than the laundry and refrigeration sides."
  },
  {
    q: "Who owns Fisher & Paykel now?",
    a: "Haier Group, since 2012. Haier (the Chinese white-goods conglomerate also headquartered in Qingdao) acquired Fisher & Paykel for approximately NZ$869 million in November 2012, and F&P became a wholly-owned subsidiary at that point. Haier subsequently acquired GE Appliances from General Electric in 2016, so Fisher & Paykel and GE Appliances now share the same ultimate parent — practical service implication: <strong>F&P parts route through the same Haier US distribution infrastructure that supports GE Appliances</strong>, which improves parts availability for LA service work compared to the pre-2012 era when F&P parts came directly from New Zealand and routinely ran 3-4 week lead times. Brand identity stays distinct (F&P is positioned as Haier's premium-luxury tier; GE Appliances spans mainstream through premium GE Profile and GE Monogram), and Fisher & Paykel engineering and design still operates out of Auckland. F&P is not related to Sub-Zero, Thermador, Miele, or any of the European luxury brands it sometimes gets compared to — different manufacturer, different parts ecosystem, different service network."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do Fisher & Paykel appliances last?",
    a: "Built for 15-20 year service life across the lineup with normal use, and well-maintained units routinely run beyond 20 years on the refrigerator and cooking sides. F&P's New Zealand engineering tradition (the brand has roots in marine-climate manufacturing — Auckland is a coastal city with humidity and salt-air conditions roughly comparable to coastal LA) produces appliances that age well in our service environment. Component wear is predictable: DishDrawer latch mechanism at year 5-6 on the 2016-2021 DD60 cohort (the dominant LA failure pattern); washer drum bearing at year 7-10; dryer heating element at year 6-8; refrigerator ActiveSmart control board at year 8-12; refrigerator compressor at year 12-15 typical. What this means for repair-vs-replace economics: <strong>F&P replacement-unit pricing runs $2,000-$5,000 per appliance — repair almost always makes financial sense</strong>. A $385 DishDrawer latch swap on a 6-year-old DD60 (replacement value around $2,800) is obvious math. Even at year 12 with a $680-$980 compressor replacement on an RF170 (replacement value around $4,500), repair stays in the right side of the calculation. We tell you the numbers at diagnostic before authorization, but the F&P repair-vs-replace conversation is shorter than it is on most brands because the math is so consistently on the repair side."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find official Fisher & Paykel warranty info?",
    a: `Our technicians work independently of F&P's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
  }
];

