    <p class="section-number">07, Where we go</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Fisher &amp; Paykel service across Greater Los Angeles.</h2>

    <p>Fisher &amp; Paykel cluster patterns track the design-conscious mid-luxury demographic in our service area. Venice and Silver Lake account for the largest concentration of F&amp;P kitchens we service — open-plan mid-century renovations where the DishDrawer drawer aesthetic fits the minimalist millwork and the RF-series French door refrigerator's panel-ready integrated variants fit the cabinet-flush design language. Mar Vista and West LA contemporary builds follow the same pattern. Malibu carries a meaningful share of the F&amp;P washer/dryer volume — the New Zealand engineering tradition's marine-climate corrosion resistance aligns well with beach-adjacent properties where coastal salt-air shortens the service life of less-corrosion-tolerant brands. Pacific Palisades and Bel Air pick up larger custom kitchens where F&amp;P gets specified alongside Sub-Zero columns or Wolf ranges as the laundry and dishwasher counterpart. Less concentrated but recurring: Pasadena craftsman renovations, Studio City and Sherman Oaks Valley kitchens, Newport Beach OC properties. The 8-branch dispatch grid in the hero CTA shows the closest dispatch territory; our technician arrives with common F&amp;P DD60 latches, RF-series evaporator fans, and WH/DE laundry parts on the truck for same-day completion when symptoms can be identified by phone before the visit.</p>
